         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Paddington Village Plot 10 Hotel Operator</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN335138</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="55100000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Liverpool City Council are leading on major mixed-use development called Paddington Village in the heart of the City’s Knowledge Quarter. The Council are looking to fund and develop a high quality hotel and are seeking to procure a Hotel Operator. A procurement process is underway for a hotel brand. It is envisaged this process will be finalised following the appointment of the Hotel Operator.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKD72"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>LIverpool.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Liverpool City Council are undertaking a bespoke process with negotiation to procure a Hotel Operator. The Council are leading on major mixed-use development called Paddington Village in the heart of the City’s Knowledge Quarter. The Council are looking to fund and develop a high quality hotel and are seeking to procure a Hotel Operator. A procurement process is underway for a hotel brand. It is envisaged this process will be finalised following the appointment of the Hotel Operator. ACC Liverpool, a bespoke Liverpool City owned management team, operate and manage the Arena and Convention Centre Liverpool a world-class leisure and convention complex. Within this structure, “ACC Hotels” successfully runs the Pullman Hotel under a Franchise with a management agreement with a Hotel Operating Company. There is an option that the hotel at PV could be added to this group of assets under a further subsidiary of ACC Liverpool with the management and marketing of the hotel falling within the existing operational and commercial arrangements.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">120</DURATION>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>Although the contract length is expected to be around 10 years. It is anticipated that the initial length and any extension options will be agreed through negotiation of the Heads of Terms. Details are provided within the tender documentation.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
